SARS Commissioner Edward Kieswetter will give an update on his first month in office. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - New South African Revenue Service commissioner Edward Kieswetter will give an update on his first month in office. He is expected to discuss a range of issues, including the 2019 tax season as well as the Nugent Commission Report. READ: Eskom debt expected to worsen: experts Kieswetter was appointed in March and replaced Mark Kingon who was acting in the position after Tom Moyane was relieved of his duties. He was SARS deputy commissioner from 2004 to 2008. Kieswetter was recently Alexander Forbes Group Chief Executive.